\section*{Preface}

This document presents a unified field-theoretic framework for modeling
consciousness as a dynamical process on a smooth configuration manifold.
The theory is constructed in layers: a mathematically rigorous core,
followed by gauge, quantum, and BRST extensions. Each layer is internally
consistent and reduces to the previous one when additional structure is
removed.

The goal is not to impose a specific physical substrate but to provide a
universal mathematical architecture capable of describing biological,
artificial, and simulated systems. The theory is falsifiable through
dynamical, stochastic, and thermodynamic predictions, and is suitable
for empirical testing.

This monograph-style presentation includes a notation table, glossary,
and structured appendices to support clarity and reproducibility.

