\section*{Glossary}

\paragraph{Configuration manifold ($\mathcal{M}$).}
The abstract space of all possible conscious states, independent of
physical substrate.

\paragraph{Universal potential ($\Phi$).}
A scalar field encoding information, energetic, and causal structure.
Generates deterministic, stochastic, and quantum dynamics.

\paragraph{IEC functionals.}
Three smooth maps $F_I$, $F_E$, and $F_C$ encoding information,
energetic, and causal properties of a state.

\paragraph{Gauge extension.}
An advanced layer introducing a Lie-group connection $A$ and curvature
$F$, enabling additional causal structure.

\paragraph{BRST symmetry.}
A cohomological symmetry ensuring gauge consistency at the quantum
level; requires vanishing anomaly coefficients.

\paragraph{Correlation length ($\xi$).}
A measurable quantity predicting how fluctuations decay across the
manifold; diverges at phase transitions.

\paragraph{Kramers escape.}
A stochastic prediction for escape times from metastable basins,
dependent on $\Delta\Phi$ and effective temperature.

\paragraph{Resonance frequencies.}
Local oscillation frequencies near stable equilibria, derived from the
Hessian of $\Phi$.

\paragraph{Substrate mapping.}
A smooth map from the state space of a physical or artificial system
into $\mathcal{M}$, enabling empirical application.

